======================================================================

FUNCTION: vec_copy

DESCRIPTION: Copy a vector (either row vector or column vector)
             from a matrix.

REQUIRES: ---

BUGS: ---

FUTURE IMPROVEMENTS: ---

----------------------------------------------------------------------

PROCESS DESCRIPTION:

  mat_copy_column(addr_srcMat:ESI,
                  src_jumpSize:EBX,
                  addr_dstMat:EDI,
                  dst_jumpSize:EDX,
                  numOfElements:ECX)

  Input parameters
      1) addr_srcMat   = Address to the source vector
      2) src_jumpSize  = ROWSIZE if column vector, otherwise COLUMNSIZE
      3) addr_dstMat   = Address to the destination vector
      4) dst_jumpSize  = ROWSIZE if column vector, otherwise COLUMNSIZE
      5) numOfElements = Number of elements to copy

  Output parameters
      3) addr_dstMat = Filled with data from source vector

  Returns
      ---

  +-------------------------------------------------------------+
  |                   STACK MEMORY INFORMATION                  |
  +--------+----------------------------------------------------+
  | Offset |      Data       |           Description            |
  +--------+-----------------+----------------------------------+
  | +    0 | ---             | ---                              |
  |        |                 |                                  |
  +--------+-----------------+----------------------------------+
  | Total stack used for local variables =  0 bytes             |
  +-------------------------------------------------------------+

  Algorithm/Pseudocode is in "scilab/vec_copy.sce"

======================================================================
